= Mandate on the National Unions & their Responsibilities

# this should open up some new options for eco

With the beginning of our new Economic Policy, there exists a need to redefine the role of the trade unions and their responsibilities in a rapidly changing economic environment. Though naturally a significant force before the revolution, the unions have no defined role in the current economy that should be resolved immediately, considering its weight and importance to both the workers and the state.

Four proposals have been brought forward, each supported by a faction of the party, seeking to push forward their agenda. 

The first option, as proposed by the more radical members of the <span style="color: #740000ff">**Left**</span>, would be to **integrate the unions directly into state apparatus**. This would allow us greater control over management and to promote the party and educate the workers, as well as being able to work closely to both the unions and the workers to further economic recovery. This proposal has been met with immediate uproar from the Labour Reformists [? if syndicalist_active : and Syndicalists ?], who have declared complete opposition and a walkout if adopted as our plan, turning many of the trade unions into our enemies.

The second proposal would greatly expand the powers of the unions, granting them direct control of the workplace to manage production, as proposed by the Syndicalists. This has been met with criticism by members of both sides of the party, viewing a fragmented leadership and system of economic control unstable, especially in such times of economic crisis. Nevertheless, this remains an option.

The third and final proposal, would be to have the unions serve as a 'School of Communism', educating the workers and preparing them for the administration of the economy, allowing them to retain independence as well, arguing cooperation rather than coercion would serve the worker better. [? if (year = 1921 and month = 3 and week >= 3) or (year = 1921 and month > 3) or year >= 1921 : This is also the position enshrined and agreed upon by Lenin, and we will probably see an improvement in relations shall we adopt tendencies similar to their own. ?]

