Through a broad consensus opposed only by radicals of both ends, the unions continue to retain their autonomy outside the state, operating in an educational capacity to teach our workers and prepare them for the eventual control of production. In practise, this proposal does minimal change to the operations of the unions, and much of the status quo is preserved.

